      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky race to kick off the card with a few of these facing the starter for the first time. Of the raced brigade ICYMISS (7) resumes here but showed enough in her first preparation to warrant consideration in a race of this nature. Revved up for this with two solid metro trials and should be right there at the business end. MUSEE DU LOUVRE (5) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up in both efforts over this track and trip and strikes a winnable contest here. Looms as the main danger. Former NSW galloper BRITISH NAVY (4) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what he faced down south. Could be one at odds. BLUE TOES (3) gets Wiggins on board from the inside alley and shouldn't be discounted lightly. JUNGLE WONDER (2) is on debut but has shown ability at the trials and any market support must be noted.",
